<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-09-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-09-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="468" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d468">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Foster</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Newberry</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-09-07"><hi rend="italic">September 7,
                            1892</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 377.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your Nos. 517 and 518 of the
                        20th ultimo, and your No. 520 of the 23d ultimo, relative to the outrages
                        perpetrated, apparently under instigation of Armenians, on the property of
                        the Rev. Mr. Bartlett, an American citizen, at Bourdour.</p>
                    <p>Awaiting the receipt of further correspondence, and especially of the answer
                        to your note demanding reparation and security for the future, which you
                        were about to transmit to the Porte on the date of your No. 520,</p>
                    <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John W. Foster.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>